&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We require a part time HCA to work across our 2 sites in Atherton.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job Summary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To perform Healthcare Assistant tasks (such as taking blood and other samples from patients, new patient health checks), in an outpatient clinic,. Liaise with patients to provide a bespoke service, focusing on a professional and caring approach.  The postholder will be expected to support the Practice Nurses with day to day duties within their range of competencies.  Full training and support will be provided.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Skills and Qualifications:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;HCA &amp; Phlebotomy experience taking blood &amp; other samples, infection control, professional and caring, excellent attention to detail, proactive approach to running &amp; preparing clinics, helpful &amp; willing approach to working alongside GP and Practice Nurse to optimize patient health care. HCA Care Certifcate Qualification. Knowledge of Emis system data input.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
